BME280 register block at 0xF7: pressure (3 bytes MSB), temperature (3 bytes MSB), humidity (2 bytes MSB). The low nibbles of byte 2 (pressure XLSB, temp XLSB) carry the lower 4 bits.

```ts
import { ConduytDevice } from 'conduyt-js'
import { SerialTransport } from 'conduyt-js/transports/serial'

const device = await ConduytDevice.connect(
  new SerialTransport({ path: '/dev/ttyACM0' })
)
const i2c = device.i2c()
const r = await i2c.readReg(0x76, 0xF7, 8)

const pressureRaw    = (r[0] << 12) | (r[1] << 4) | (r[2] >> 4)
const temperatureRaw = (r[3] << 12) | (r[4] << 4) | (r[5] >> 4)
const humidityRaw    = (r[6] << 8)  | r[7]

console.log({ temperatureRaw, pressureRaw, humidityRaw })
```

`device.capabilities.modules` is an array of `ModuleDescriptor`. A simple `.some` covers the check.

```ts
